reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars I've bought a lot of cases for phones, but this one fit the least comfortably.
reviews.reviewText: It doesn't really tell you that it's an actual two-piece case and the plastic part actually snaps in with like eight different snaps along the frame, which the plastic is snapping into the rubber which is like a harder rubber in the first place so I could not get the phone to go in without taking the plastic part off of the rubber normally you have a flexible rubber case that goes over the phone and the plastic part kind of just pops in over top power this one is made to look like one piece and how some of them are one pieces that aren't meant to come apart so it took me a minute to figure that out mainly because the plastic snaps into the hard rubber so many places that it is very snug which isn't necessarily A bad thing however there's not much give to the rubber at all - so when I put the phone in the case and completely together and had the screen protector on it the edges of the case push the screen protector to where it comes up off of the screen especially when you're trying to press the power and volume to take a screenshot and I'm not sure if it's the phone or the screen protector but it does not lay flush all the way around the screen at the very top of the viewable screen and the very bottom of the viewable screen you can see that it doesn't properly touch how the screen is extended about an eighth of an inch further than the viewable screen so there's that black border and where the screen meets the Black border the screen protector has air all the way across underneath of it on the top and bottom both and you can't get it out almost as if the screen protector isn't made for the screen or the screen isn't completely flush when it was made obviously something's going on there. I'm going to buy a new glass screen protector and see if that fixes that issue however it's almost like the screen protector is a 2 mm to wide or something on both sides.Lastly the finger holder ring does not spin at all it's stationary which kind of sucks.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Screen saver sucks
reviews.reviewText: I got this product so my celero3 5g+ wouldn't break. I didn't like how hard it was to separate the body parts. There were no instructions on how to use this product. My biggest issue was the screen saver that came with the case. My phone is brand new and still had the plastic on the screen. I did the steps required but ended up with the lower inch part of the screen not sticking. No, my screen was clean and get. I also didn't touch the screen saver. Frustrated, I just put the phone into the case. Figured I'd work on it after it was in its case. Nope! The case side pushed so the edges up. Had to take it off, which meant there was no way it would stick on. Not happy that I have to order a separate screensaver. We'll come back and update after I've had this case for more than a month. I have a bad tendency to drop my phones.
